 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utedronaithekinslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tedronai the Kinslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/24/01 2:10:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need Advise</span><hr size=1> Well it all depends how much you want to twink your rogue with.  If I remade my rogue (halfling) I would pump sta and then str.  With raid buffs, it is very easy to get 255 str and my sta is always lacking.  Even tho, we don't get hit often, that extra sta helps a good amount.  <br>
<br>
Cheap decent weapons be blood point, crystalline short sword, trak tooth, crystalline fang.  Any of these would be pretty good.  If I went with more expensive weapons, I would get a lath drinor or seb zerker dirk in main and a CBoL in offhand.  <br>
<br>
Hide/sneak just trains naturally.  I maxxed those pretty fast.  Sense traps is just annoying to train.  I bound that to my hide/evade key.  Also backstab trains up naturally when fighting in exp groups and not soloing.  Backstab will not go up if you backstab from the front.  That means when backstabbing solo, you will not get points.  To train picklock, go to befallen and disarm traps go to solb.  <br>
<br>
Hmm dunno much else to say.  Ask me in game if ya have any other questions.  I don't know very much but I know enough.  =)<br>
<br>
Ted <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ustabba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stabba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/24/01 2:16:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need Advise</span><hr size=1> Here's my advice as a long standing rogue on the server.<br>
<br>
If you want to be respected at high level, wear armor and use weapons that suit your level.  Bloodpoints/CSS's/etc are all level 50+ items.  A good level 1 weapons is.. Dagger*, rusty dagger.  Raw-hide armor is good as well.  Knowledge about the actual game (where to hunt, what drops items, how to move your character around [very important]) will make you a benefit to Lanys instead of being &quot;just another rogue twink.&quot;<br>
<br>
In conclusion: don't twink, but learn about playing a rogue through experience.  If you need help with minor stuff, send me a tell.. I get a lot of them a day from non-twinked rogues, and, in my opinion, there's not enough non-twinked rogues. <p>100% smart-ass -- 80% Killer -- 60% Achiever -- 33% Explorer -- 26% Socializer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubinkeefurrytoes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binkee Furrytoes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/24/01 9:49:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need Advise</span><hr size=1> /agree Stabba<br>
<br>
best way to have fun is to earn it.  learn the rogue class, instead of just being that bastard with the blood points and the red dragonscale bp who doesn't know how to evade.<br>
<br>
I know a good deal about the rogue game at a pre-planar level (still learning the rest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), so if you want advice, lemme know.<br>
<br>
I can give you a few quick hotkey tips though...at least, this is how mine are set up.<br>
<br>
1 - backstab<br>
2 - assist (on main tank)<br>
3 - sneak<br>
4 - hide (evade hotkeys = poo)<br>
5 - /em hugs %t's leg (<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
6 - Pull message (don't use most of the time, but I keep it there because I never use the 6 button <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
7 - Ranged Attack/Persona (moved ranged attack here during 45, when I decided i didn't want to see my exp bar anymore)<br>
8 - Assist (on secondary tank)<br>
9 - Disarm (useless for the most part, but gets me phat lewtz every now and then <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
0 - Pick Pockets (I don't pick, I swear!)<br>
<br>
With this setup, a normal battle for me goes something like this...<br>
<br>
Tank says, 'assist'<br>
<br>
2<br>
&lt;circle strafe&gt;<br>
a<br>
&lt;do this until mob is at 80% hps&gt;<br>
1a34<br>
&lt;wait anywhere form 1 sec to 4 secs&gt;<br>
a3 (takes sneak back off)<br>
1a0a<br>
1a09a<br>
<br>
etc...<br>
<br>
it's a good idea to have any attacks on you, misses included to show up in the bright red color, that way, if you can avoid taking damage, you can get the evade off real quick.  Without using an evade key, I evade better than most rogues I've grouped with ('course the do a hell of a lot more damage).  In a *normal* fight, if I take 100 points of damage, I'm doing something wrong, and I fix it.  In a *bad pull* situation, things are different, but for the most part, I never drop below 3 bubs.<br>
<br>
Also a good thing to learn is how to recognize when you need to sneak/hide and zone, to CR your group.  In sol B named, I can see a bad pull coming a mile away, and most times won't even fight, just sit there hidden and have everyone consent me when they have to run.<br>
<br>
